## 3. Data Flow & Architecture

**[source](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/hierarchy_builder_metadata.py#59-87) → `converter.convert()` → [result](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/postprocessor.py#81-135) (Linear Output) → `ResultPostprocessor.process()` → Final Output (Tree Structure)**

1. **Source ([source](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/hierarchy_builder_metadata.py#59-87))**: A PDF file path or stream.
2. **`converter.convert()`**: Docling loads the PDF. The vision model sees a large bold text block and labels it `SectionHeaderItem`. It sees normal text below it and labels it `TextItem`. It outputs a flat array of these items.
3. **`ResultPostprocessor.process()`**: Takes the flat list. Extracts metadata (e.g. "This heading is 24pt, the next is 18pt"). It clusters 24pt texts as H1 and 18pt texts as H2.
4. **Final Output**: The flat array is mutated into a tree. The H1 node's `.children` list now contains the H2 node and any introductory `TextItem`s.

