## 5. Code-Level Insights

### Key Classes & Methods
*   **[ResultPostprocessor](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/postprocessor.py#55-243)** (`hierarchical.postprocessor`): The main orchestrator.
*   **[HierarchyBuilderMetadata](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/hierarchy_builder_metadata.py#44-210)** (`hierarchical.hierarchy_builder_metadata`): Wrapper around PyMuPDF (`FitzDocument`) to extract exact native TOC bookmarks and map them to bounding box coordinates (`this_bbox`).
*   **[DocumentHierarchyBuilder](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/hierarchy_builder.py#26-322)** (`hierarchical.hierarchy_builder`): Used when no native TOC exists. Contains two key inference methods:
    *   [_infer_from_numbering()](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/hierarchy_builder.py#80-204): Checks regex patterns for numbers/letters (`1.`, `a.`, `I.`).
    *   [_infer_by_clustering()](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/hierarchy_builder.py#205-258): Uses `sklearn.cluster.DBSCAN` to cluster headings by font-size.
*   **[set_item_in_doc](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/postprocessor.py#48-53)**: A utility that mutates the internal Docling JSON-path-like references (e.g. swapping a `TextItem` for a `SectionHeaderItem`).

### Design Patterns
- **Pipeline / Middleware Pattern**: The postprocessor is designed to be chained immediately after the main converter execution, mutating the payload before the user serializes it (e.g. to JSON or Markdown).
- **Fallback Strategy Pattern**: [HierarchyBuilderMetadata](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/hierarchy_builder_metadata.py#44-210) attempts native TOC extraction -> falls back to Numbering Inference -> falls back to DBSCAN Style Clustering.

