```json
[
  {"type": "SectionHeaderItem", "text": "Introduction", "font_size": 20},
  {"type": "TextItem", "text": "This is the intro text."},
  {"type": "SectionHeaderItem", "text": "Background", "font_size": 14},
  {"type": "TextItem", "text": "This is background info."}
]
```
*(Note: These are all flat siblings at the root of the document)*

**Intermediate Structure (`HierarchicalHeader` Tree)**:
The clustering algorithm groups the 20pt fonts as Level 1 and 14pt as Level 2.
```
Tree:
- Root
  - Introduction (Level 1)
    - Background (Level 2)
```

**Final Processed Output**:
```json
[
  {
    "type": "SectionHeaderItem", "text": "Introduction", "level": 1,
    "children": [{"$ref": "#/Background"}, {"$ref": "#/intro_text"}]
  },
  {
    "type": "TextItem", "text": "This is the intro text.", 
    "parent": {"$ref": "#/Introduction"}
  },
  {
    "type": "SectionHeaderItem", "text": "Background", "level": 2,
    "parent": {"$ref": "#/Introduction"},
    "children": [{"$ref": "#/background_info"}]
  }
]
