## 7. Summary
The [ResultPostprocessor](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/postprocessor.py#55-243) solves the problem of **flatness** in vision-based document parsing. While [DocumentConverter](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling/document_converter.py#198-580) is excellent at classifying isolated bounding boxes (knowing *what* something is visually), it lacks the global context to know *how it relates* to the rest of the document algebraically.

By chaining [ResultPostprocessor(result).process()](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/rag_learning_materials/docling/docling-hierarchical-pdf/hierarchical/postprocessor.py#55-243) after conversion, the pipeline transforms a "dumb" visual readout of text chunks into a semantically aware, hierarchical tree. This is absolutely critical for RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) applications, as it allows document chunkers to split a PDF logically by Heading 1 or Heading 2 boundaries rather than arbitrary character limits, preserving the author's original narrative structure.
